Source of the article : Dexerto Asus Zenfone 2 Laser ZE500KL Specs, Price, Release Date, Availability
Asus Zenfone 2 Laser ZE500KL is a mid-range smartphone that was released in August 2015. It is a variant of the Asus Zenfone 2 series, which was launched earlier in the same year. The Zenfone 2 Laser ZE500KL is designed to offer a balance between performance and affordability, making it an attractive option for budget-conscious consumers.
Design and Display
The Asus Zenfone 2 Laser ZE500KL features a sleek and stylish design with a plastic body. It has a 5-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1280 pixels, resulting in a pixel density of approximately 294 pixels per inch (PPI). The display offers decent color reproduction and viewing angles, making it suitable for multimedia consumption and everyday use.
Performance and Hardware
Under the hood, the Zenfone 2 Laser ZE500KL is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 410 chipset, which is a quad-core processor clocked at 1.2 GHz. It is paired with 2GB of RAM, which provides smooth multitasking and app performance. The device comes with 16GB of internal storage, which can be expanded up to 128GB via a microSD card slot.
Camera
One of the standout features of the Asus Zenfone 2 Laser ZE500KL is its camera capabilities. It sports a 13-megapixel rear camera with laser autofocus, which enables faster and more accurate focusing. The camera also features an f/2.0 aperture, allowing for better low-light photography. On the front, there is a 5-megapixel selfie camera with an f/2.0 aperture, which captures decent self-portraits and supports video calling.
Battery and Connectivity
The Zenfone 2 Laser ZE500KL is equipped with a non-removable 2,400mAh battery, which provides a decent amount of power for a full day of moderate usage. It supports 4G LTE connectivity, allowing for fast internet browsing and downloading speeds. Other connectivity options include Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, and a microUSB 2.0 port for charging and data transfer.
Software and Features
The device runs on Android 5.0 Lollipop out of the box, with Asus' ZenUI skin on top. The ZenUI offers a range of customization options and additional features, such as gesture controls, themes, and various pre-installed apps. However, it is worth noting that the software experience may vary depending on the region and carrier.
Price and Availability
The Asus Zenfone 2 Laser ZE500KL was initially priced at around $200 USD, making it an affordable option for consumers looking for a mid-range smartphone. However, it is important to note that the availability and pricing may vary depending on the region and retailer. As of now, the device may be available through various online and offline retailers, as well as through Asus' official website.
Conclusion
The Asus Zenfone 2 Laser ZE500KL is a budget-friendly smartphone that offers a decent set of features and specifications. With its laser autofocus camera, expandable storage, and 4G LTE connectivity, it provides a good balance between performance and affordability. However, it is worth considering that the device was released in 2015, and there may be newer and more advanced options available in the market today.
